Less than 24 hours after publishers announced a July 16 release date for ``Harry Potter and the Half Blood Prince'' _British author J.K. Rowling's sixth novel set in the halls of Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry_ it had shot to No. 1 on online bookseller amazon.co.uk's Hot 100 book list. Amazon said it took 420,000 pre-orders for the fifth in the series, ``Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix,'' released in the summer of 2003, making it the largest ever pre-order item. 